  THE QUARTET:
    2: the field (F_2)
    5: the discriminant (Δ = 5b²)
    7: the projective plane (PG(2, F_2))
    τ = (1+√5)/2 = 1.6180339887

    2 + 5 = 7 (the projective plane!)
    2 · 5 = 10 = C(5,2) (arcs of the golden tournament C₅)
    7 - 5 = 2 (the field!)
    7 - 2 = 5 (the discriminant!)
    5 = F_5 (the Fibonacci fixed point)
    τ² - τ = 1 (the fundamental relation)
    τ⁵ = 5τ + 3 = 11.090170 = 11.090170

    The quartet is CLOSED under the operations:
    2 + 5 = 7, 7 - 2 = 5, 7 - 5 = 2
    These three equations are THE SAME EQUATION.
    The quartet reduces to the pair (2, 5) and the relation 2+5=7.
    τ emerges from 5 via √5.
    So ultimately: (2, 5) generates everything.
    And 5 = 2² + 1 = the successor of the square of 2.
    So STILL: only 2 is fundamental. 5 = f(2). 7 = f(2,5).

